5000|$|By {{leveraging}} {{the purchase}} of an investment property, the required periodic payments to service the debt create an ongoing (and sometimes large) negative cash flow beginning {{from the time of}} purchase. This is sometimes referred to as the <b>carry</b> <b>cost</b> or [...] "carry" [...] of the investment. To be successful, real estate investors must manage their cash flows to create enough positive income from the property to at least offset the <b>carry</b> <b>costs.</b>|$|R
